The paper focuses on reducing the memory bandwidth requirements of CNNs for low-power edge devices, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The approach involves lossy transform coding, which is a technique used in image and video compression (cs.AR). The paper also discusses the implementation of the approach on FPGA hardware, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
